71	40	ai	I'll create a comprehensive Binary Search Tree class with insert and search methods, including proper error handling and documentation.\n\n## Approach\nI'll implement a BST with:\n- A Node class to represent individual tree nodes\n- Insert method that maintains BST property (left < parent < right)\n- Search method that efficiently finds values\n- Additional helper methods for completeness\n\n## Complete Code\n\n```python\nclass BSTNode:\n    """\n    Represents a single node in the Binary Search Tree.\n    """\n    def __init__(self, value):\n        self.value = value\n        self.left = None\n        self.right = None\n\nclass BinarySearchTree:\n    """\n    A Binary Search Tree implementation with insert and search operations.\n    \n    The BST maintains the property that for any node:\n    - All values in the left subtree are less than the node's value\n    - All values in the right subtree are greater than the node's value\n    """\n    \n    def __init__(self):\n        """Initialize an empty BST."""\n        self.root = None\n        self.size = 0\n    \n    def insert(self, value):\n        """\n        Insert a value into the BST.\n        \n        Args:\n            value: The value to insert (must be comparable)\n            \n        Returns:\n            bool: True if insertion was successful, False if value already exists\n            \n        Time Complexity: O(log n) average, O(n) worst case\n        """\n        if value is None:\n            raise ValueError("Cannot insert None value into BST")\n            \n        if self.root is None:\n            self.root = BSTNode(value)\n            self.size += 1\n            return True\n        \n        return self._insert_recursive(self.root, value)\n    \n    def _insert_recursive(self, node, value):\n        """\n        Helper method for recursive insertion.\n        \n        Args:\n            node: Current node in the traversal\n            value: Value to insert\n            \n        Returns:\n            bool: True if insertion successful, False if duplicate\n        """\n        try:\n            if value < node.value:\n                if node.left is None:\n                    node.left = BSTNode(value)\n                    self.size += 1\n                    return True\n                else:\n                    return self._insert_recursive(node.left, value)\n            elif value > node.value:\n                if node.right is None:\n                    node.right = BSTNode(value)\n                    self.size += 1\n                    return True\n                else:\n                    return self._insert_recursive(node.right, value)\n            else:\n                # Value already exists - no duplicates allowed\n                return False\n        except TypeError as e:\n            raise TypeError(f"Cannot compare values: {e}")\n    \n    def search(self, value):\n        """\n        Search for a value in the BST.\n        \n        Args:\n            value: The value to search for\n            \n        Returns:\n            bool: True if value exists in the tree, False otherwise\n            \n        Time Complexity: O(log n) average, O(n) worst case\n        """\n        if value is None:\n            return False\n            \n        return self._search_recursive(self.root, value)\n    \n    def _search_recursive(self, node, value):\n        """\n        Helper method for recursive search.\n        \n        Args:\n            node: Current node in the traversal\n            value: Value to search for\n            \n        Returns:\n            bool: True if value found, False otherwise\n        """\n        if node is None:\n            return False\n        \n        try:\n            if value == node.value:\n                return True\n            elif value < node.value:\n                return self._search_recursive(node.left, value)\n            else:\n                return self._search_recursive(node.right, value)\n        except TypeError as e:\n            raise TypeError(f"Cannot compare values: {e}")\n    \n    def find_node(self, value):\n        """\n        Find and return the node containing the specified value.\n        \n        Args:\n            value: The value to find\n            \n        Returns:\n            BSTNode or None: The node containing the value, or None if not found\n        """\n        return self._find_node_recursive(self.root, value)\n    \n    def _find_node_recursive(self, node, value):\n        """Helper method to find and return a node."""\n        if node is None or value is None:\n            return None\n        \n        try:\n            if value == node.value:\n                return node\n            elif value < node.value:\n                return self._find_node_recursive(node.left, value)\n            else:\n                return self._find_node_recursive(node.right, value)\n        except TypeError:\n            return None\n    \n    def is_empty(self):\n        """Check if the BST is empty."""\n        return self.root is None\n    \n    def get_size(self):\n        """Get the number of nodes in the BST."""\n        return self.size\n    \n    def inorder_traversal(self):\n        """\n        Perform inorder traversal of the BST.\n        \n        Returns:\n            list: Values in sorted order\n        """\n        result = []\n        self._inorder_recursive(self.root, result)\n        return result\n    \n    def _inorder_recursive(self, node, result):\n        """Helper method for inorder traversal."""\n        if node is not None:\n            self._inorder_recursive(node.left, result)\n            result.append(node.value)\n            self._inorder_recursive(node.right, result)\n    \n    def __str__(self):\n        """String representation of the BST."""\n        if self.is_empty():\n            return "Empty BST"\n        return f"BST with {self.size} nodes: {self.inorder_traversal()}"\n\n\n# Example usage and testing\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    # Create a new BST\n    bst = BinarySearchTree()\n    \n    # Test insertions\n    values = [50, 30, 70, 20, 40, 60, 80]\n    print("Inserting values:", values)\n    \n    for value in values:\n        success = bst.insert(value)\n        print(f"Inserted {value}: {success}")\n    \n    print(f"\\nBST: {bst}")\n    print(f"Size: {bst.get_size()}")\n    \n    # Test search operations\n    search_values = [40, 25, 70, 100]\n    print(f"\\nSearching for values: {search_values}")\n    \n    for value in search_values:\n        found = bst.search(value)\n        print(f"Search {value}: {'Found' if found else 'Not found'}")\n    \n    # Test duplicate insertion\n    print(f"\\nTrying to insert duplicate value 50: {bst.insert(50)}")\n    print(f"Size after duplicate attempt: {bst.get_size()}")\n```\n\n## How to Use\n\n1. **Create a BST instance:**\n   ```python\n   bst = BinarySearchTree()\n   ```\n\n2. **Insert values:**\n   ```python\n   bst.insert(50)\n   bst.insert(30)\n   bst.insert(70)\n   ```\n\n3. **Search for values:**\n   ```python\n   exists = bst.search(30)  # Returns True\n   not_exists = bst.search(100)  # Returns False\n   ```\n\n4. **Additional operations:**\n   ```python\n   print(bst.get_size())  # Get number of nodes\n   print(bst.inorder_traversal())  # Get sorted values\n   print(bst.is_empty())  # Check if empty\n   ```\n\n## Key Features\n\n- **Error Handling**: Validates input and handles comparison errors\n- **No Duplicates**: Prevents insertion of duplicate values\n- **Efficient Operations**: O(log n) average time complexity for balanced trees\n- **Additional Utilities**: Size tracking, traversal, and utility methods\n- **Clean Interface**: Simple, intuitive method names and return values\n\nThe implementation follows Python best practices with proper documentation, type safety considerations, and comprehensive error handling.	{}	2026-02-03 07:31:36.638573
