291	134	ai	I'll create a robust palindrome checker function with multiple approaches and proper error handling.\n\n## Approach\nI'll provide a comprehensive solution that:\n1. Handles case-insensitive comparison\n2. Optionally ignores spaces and punctuation\n3. Includes proper error handling\n4. Offers both simple and advanced versions\n\n## Code Implementation\n\n```python\nimport re\nfrom typing import Optional\n\ndef is_palindrome(text: str, ignore_case: bool = True, ignore_non_alphanumeric: bool = True) -> bool:\n    """\n    Check if a given string is a palindrome.\n    \n    A palindrome reads the same forwards and backwards.\n    \n    Args:\n        text (str): The string to check\n        ignore_case (bool): Whether to ignore case differences (default: True)\n        ignore_non_alphanumeric (bool): Whether to ignore spaces, punctuation, etc. (default: True)\n    \n    Returns:\n        bool: True if the string is a palindrome, False otherwise\n    \n    Raises:\n        TypeError: If input is not a string\n        \n    Examples:\n        >>> is_palindrome("racecar")\n        True\n        >>> is_palindrome("A man a plan a canal Panama")\n        True\n        >>> is_palindrome("race a car")\n        False\n        >>> is_palindrome("hello")\n        False\n    """\n    # Input validation\n    if not isinstance(text, str):\n        raise TypeError(f"Expected string, got {type(text).__name__}")\n    \n    # Handle empty string (considered a palindrome)\n    if not text:\n        return True\n    \n    # Process the string based on options\n    processed_text = text\n    \n    if ignore_case:\n        processed_text = processed_text.lower()\n    \n    if ignore_non_alphanumeric:\n        # Keep only alphanumeric characters\n        processed_text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9]', '', processed_text)\n    \n    # Check if the processed string equals its reverse\n    return processed_text == processed_text[::-1]\n\n\ndef is_palindrome_simple(text: str) -> bool:\n    """\n    Simple palindrome checker (case-sensitive, includes all characters).\n    \n    Args:\n        text (str): The string to check\n    \n    Returns:\n        bool: True if the string is a palindrome, False otherwise\n    \n    Examples:\n        >>> is_palindrome_simple("racecar")\n        True\n        >>> is_palindrome_simple("Racecar")\n        False\n    """\n    if not isinstance(text, str):\n        raise TypeError(f"Expected string, got {type(text).__name__}")\n    \n    return text == text[::-1]\n\n\ndef is_palindrome_iterative(text: str, ignore_case: bool = True, ignore_non_alphanumeric: bool = True) -> bool:\n    """\n    Check palindrome using two-pointer approach (more memory efficient for very long strings).\n    \n    Args:\n        text (str): The string to check\n        ignore_case (bool): Whether to ignore case differences\n        ignore_non_alphanumeric (bool): Whether to ignore non-alphanumeric characters\n    \n    Returns:\n        bool: True if the string is a palindrome, False otherwise\n    """\n    if not isinstance(text, str):\n        raise TypeError(f"Expected string, got {type(text).__name__}")\n    \n    if not text:\n        return True\n    \n    # Process the string\n    processed_text = text\n    if ignore_case:\n        processed_text = processed_text.lower()\n    if ignore_non_alphanumeric:\n        processed_text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9]', '', processed_text)\n    \n    # Two-pointer approach\n    left, right = 0, len(processed_text) - 1\n    \n    while left < right:\n        if processed_text[left] != processed_text[right]:\n            return False\n        left += 1\n        right -= 1\n    \n    return True\n\n\n# Example usage and testing\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    # Test cases\n    test_cases = [\n        "racecar",\n        "A man a plan a canal Panama",\n        "race a car",\n        "hello",\n        "",\n        "Madam",\n        "Was it a car or a cat I saw?",\n        "No 'x' in Nixon",\n        "Mr. Owl ate my metal worm"\n    ]\n    \n    print("Testing palindrome checker:")\n    print("-" * 50)\n    \n    for test in test_cases:\n        result = is_palindrome(test)\n        simple_result = is_palindrome_simple(test.replace(" ", "").replace("'", "").replace("?", "").replace(",", "").replace(".", "").lower())\n        \n        print(f"'{test}' -> {result}")\n    \n    print("\\nTesting simple version (case-sensitive, exact match):")\n    print("-" * 50)\n    \n    simple_tests = ["racecar", "Racecar", "level", "hello"]\n    for test in simple_tests:\n        result = is_palindrome_simple(test)\n        print(f"'{test}' -> {result}")\n```\n\n## How to Use\n\n### Basic Usage\n```python\n# Default behavior: ignore case and non-alphanumeric characters\nresult = is_palindrome("A man a plan a canal Panama")  # Returns True\n\n# Simple exact match\nresult = is_palindrome_simple("racecar")  # Returns True\nresult = is_palindrome_simple("Racecar")  # Returns False\n```\n\n### Advanced Usage\n```python\n# Case-sensitive palindrome check\nresult = is_palindrome("Racecar", ignore_case=False)  # Returns False\n\n# Include all characters (spaces, punctuation)\nresult = is_palindrome("race car", ignore_non_alphanumeric=False)  # Returns False\n\n# Memory-efficient version for very long strings\nresult = is_palindrome_iterative("A very long palindrome string...")\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n1. **Flexible Options**: Choose whether to ignore case and/or non-alphanumeric characters\n2. **Error Handling**: Proper type checking with descriptive error messages\n3. **Multiple Implementations**: String slicing and two-pointer approaches\n4. **Comprehensive Testing**: Includes various test cases\n5. **Documentation**: Full docstrings with examples\n6. **Type Hints**: Modern Python typing for better IDE support\n\nThe main `is_palindrome()` function is recommended for most use cases as it provides the most flexibility and handles common palindrome scenarios intuitively.	{}	2026-02-03 10:07:52.798289
