305	141	ai	I'll create a comprehensive TypeScript User interface with optional fields that would be commonly used in applications.\n\n## Approach\nI'll design a User interface that includes both required fields (like id and email) and optional fields (like profile information, preferences, etc.). This follows common patterns where core identification is required but additional profile data is optional.\n\n## Code\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Represents a user in the system with core required fields and optional profile information\n */\ninterface User {\n  // Required fields - core identification\n  readonly id: string;\n  email: string;\n  \n  // Optional profile information\n  firstName?: string;\n  lastName?: string;\n  username?: string;\n  displayName?: string;\n  \n  // Optional contact information\n  phoneNumber?: string;\n  address?: {\n    street?: string;\n    city?: string;\n    state?: string;\n    zipCode?: string;\n    country?: string;\n  };\n  \n  // Optional metadata\n  dateOfBirth?: Date;\n  profilePictureUrl?: string;\n  bio?: string;\n  \n  // Optional system fields\n  isActive?: boolean;\n  isVerified?: boolean;\n  lastLoginAt?: Date;\n  createdAt?: Date;\n  updatedAt?: Date;\n  \n  // Optional preferences\n  preferences?: {\n    theme?: 'light' | 'dark' | 'auto';\n    language?: string;\n    timezone?: string;\n    notifications?: {\n      email?: boolean;\n      push?: boolean;\n      sms?: boolean;\n    };\n  };\n  \n  // Optional role/permissions\n  role?: 'admin' | 'user' | 'moderator';\n  permissions?: string[];\n}\n\n/**\n * Type for creating a new user - only requires essential fields\n */\ntype CreateUserInput = Pick<User, 'email'> & Partial<Omit<User, 'id' | 'createdAt' | 'updatedAt'>>;\n\n/**\n * Type for updating an existing user - all fields optional except id\n */\ntype UpdateUserInput = Pick<User, 'id'> & Partial<Omit<User, 'id' | 'createdAt'>>;\n```\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n```typescript\n// Example 1: Minimal user with only required fields\nconst minimalUser: User = {\n  id: "user-123",\n  email: "john.doe@example.com"\n};\n\n// Example 2: Complete user profile\nconst completeUser: User = {\n  id: "user-456",\n  email: "jane.smith@example.com",\n  firstName: "Jane",\n  lastName: "Smith",\n  username: "janesmith",\n  displayName: "Jane S.",\n  phoneNumber: "+1-555-0123",\n  address: {\n    street: "123 Main St",\n    city: "Anytown",\n    state: "CA",\n    zipCode: "12345",\n    country: "USA"\n  },\n  dateOfBirth: new Date("1990-05-15"),\n  profilePictureUrl: "https://example.com/avatar.jpg",\n  bio: "Software developer passionate about TypeScript",\n  isActive: true,\n  isVerified: true,\n  lastLoginAt: new Date(),\n  createdAt: new Date("2023-01-01"),\n  updatedAt: new Date(),\n  preferences: {\n    theme: "dark",\n    language: "en",\n    timezone: "America/Los_Angeles",\n    notifications: {\n      email: true,\n      push: false,\n      sms: true\n    }\n  },\n  role: "user",\n  permissions: ["read:profile", "update:profile"]\n};\n\n// Example 3: Creating a new user\nconst newUserData: CreateUserInput = {\n  email: "newuser@example.com",\n  firstName: "New",\n  lastName: "User",\n  preferences: {\n    theme: "light"\n  }\n};\n\n// Example 4: Updating an existing user\nconst userUpdate: UpdateUserInput = {\n  id: "user-123",\n  firstName: "Updated",\n  preferences: {\n    theme: "dark",\n    notifications: {\n      email: false\n    }\n  }\n};\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n1. **Required vs Optional**: Core fields like `id` and `email` are required, while profile information is optional\n2. **Readonly ID**: The `id` field is readonly to prevent accidental modification\n3. **Nested Optional Objects**: Complex objects like `address` and `preferences` have optional properties\n4. **Union Types**: Used for constrained values like `theme` and `role`\n5. **Utility Types**: Included `CreateUserInput` and `UpdateUserInput` for common operations\n6. **Type Safety**: All optional fields use the `?` operator for proper TypeScript checking\n\nThis interface provides flexibility for different use cases while maintaining type safety and clear documentation of what fields are available.	{}	2026-02-03 10:12:49.994001
