327	147	ai	I'll create a `useDebounce` hook that delays updating a value until after a specified period of inactivity. This is commonly used for search inputs, API calls, or any scenario where you want to wait for the user to stop typing before performing an action.\n\n## Approach\nThe hook will use `useState` to store the debounced value and `useEffect` to manage a timeout that updates the debounced value after the delay period. If the input value changes before the timeout completes, we'll clear the previous timeout and start a new one.\n\n## Complete Code\n\n```typescript\nimport { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\n\n/**\n * Custom hook that debounces a value, delaying updates until after a specified delay period\n * has passed without changes. Useful for search inputs, API calls, or any scenario where\n * you want to wait for user input to stabilize before performing an action.\n * \n * @param value - The value to debounce (can be any type)\n * @param delay - Delay in milliseconds before updating the debounced value\n * @returns The debounced value that only updates after the delay period\n * \n * @example\n * ```tsx\n * const [searchTerm, setSearchTerm] = useState('');\n * const debouncedSearchTerm = useDebounce(searchTerm, 500);\n * \n * // Use debouncedSearchTerm for API calls\n * useEffect(() => {\n *   if (debouncedSearchTerm) {\n *     searchAPI(debouncedSearchTerm);\n *   }\n * }, [debouncedSearchTerm]);\n * ```\n */\nfunction useDebounce<T>(value: T, delay: number): T {\n  // State to store the debounced value\n  const [debouncedValue, setDebouncedValue] = useState<T>(value);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    // Set up a timeout to update the debounced value after the delay\n    const timeoutId = setTimeout(() => {\n      setDebouncedValue(value);\n    }, delay);\n\n    // Cleanup function: clear the timeout if value changes before delay completes\n    // This ensures that the debounced value only updates after the user stops\n    // changing the input for the full delay period\n    return () => {\n      clearTimeout(timeoutId);\n    };\n  }, [value, delay]); // Re-run effect when value or delay changes\n\n  return debouncedValue;\n}\n\nexport default useDebounce;\n```\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Basic Search Input Example\n```tsx\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\nimport useDebounce from './useDebounce';\n\nfunction SearchComponent() {\n  const [searchTerm, setSearchTerm] = useState('');\n  const [results, setResults] = useState([]);\n  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);\n  \n  // Debounce search term with 500ms delay\n  const debouncedSearchTerm = useDebounce(searchTerm, 500);\n\n  // Perform search when debounced term changes\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (debouncedSearchTerm) {\n      setIsLoading(true);\n      searchAPI(debouncedSearchTerm)\n        .then(setResults)\n        .finally(() => setIsLoading(false));\n    } else {\n      setResults([]);\n    }\n  }, [debouncedSearchTerm]);\n\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <input\n        type="text"\n        placeholder="Search..."\n        value={searchTerm}\n        onChange={(e) => setSearchTerm(e.target.value)}\n      />\n      {isLoading && <p>Searching...</p>}\n      {/* Render results */}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Form Validation Example\n```tsx\nimport React, { useState } from 'react';\nimport useDebounce from './useDebounce';\n\nfunction EmailInput() {\n  const [email, setEmail] = useState('');\n  const [isValid, setIsValid] = useState(true);\n  \n  // Debounce email validation with 300ms delay\n  const debouncedEmail = useDebounce(email, 300);\n\n  // Validate email when debounced value changes\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (debouncedEmail) {\n      const emailRegex = /^[^\\s@]+@[^\\s@]+\\.[^\\s@]+$/;\n      setIsValid(emailRegex.test(debouncedEmail));\n    }\n  }, [debouncedEmail]);\n\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <input\n        type="email"\n        value={email}\n        onChange={(e) => setEmail(e.target.value)}\n        className={!isValid ? 'error' : ''}\n      />\n      {!isValid && <span>Please enter a valid email</span>}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n1. **Generic Type Support**: Works with any data type (string, number, object, etc.)\n2. **Proper Cleanup**: Clears timeouts to prevent memory leaks\n3. **Immediate Initial Value**: Returns the initial value immediately, then debounces subsequent changes\n4. **TypeScript Support**: Full type safety with generic parameter\n5. **Flexible Delay**: Configurable delay period for different use cases\n\n## Common Use Cases\n\n- **Search inputs**: Wait for user to stop typing before making API calls\n- **Form validation**: Delay validation until user pauses input\n- **Auto-save**: Save form data after user stops editing\n- **Resize handlers**: Debounce window resize events\n- **API rate limiting**: Prevent excessive API calls\n\nThe hook is lightweight, reusable, and follows React best practices for custom hooks.	{}	2026-02-03 10:40:06.464128
