331	149	ai	Here's a concise comparison between processes and threads:\n\n| Aspect | Process | Thread |\n|--------|---------|--------|\n| **Definition** | Independent program in execution | Lightweight unit within a process |\n| **Memory** | Separate memory space | Shared memory space within process |\n| **Creation Cost** | High (expensive) | Low (lightweight) |\n| **Context Switching** | Slower (more overhead) | Faster (less overhead) |\n| **Communication** | IPC mechanisms (pipes, sockets) | Direct memory sharing |\n| **Isolation** | Fully isolated from other processes | Share resources with other threads |\n| **Crash Impact** | Doesn't affect other processes | Can crash entire process |\n| **Resource Sharing** | No direct sharing | Share code, data, files |\n| **Scheduling** | Scheduled by OS independently | Scheduled within process context |\n| **Examples** | Web browser, text editor | Browser tabs, worker threads |\n\n**Key Takeaway**: Processes are independent programs with their own memory, while threads are lightweight execution units that share memory within a single process.	{}	2026-02-03 10:43:07.147045
