345	149	ai	The time complexity of quicksort is:\n\n**Best case: O(n log n)**\n- Occurs when the pivot always divides the array into two nearly equal halves\n- Each level of recursion processes n elements, and there are log n levels\n\n**Average case: O(n log n)**\n- On average, the pivot divides the array reasonably well\n- Mathematical analysis shows this averages to O(n log n)\n\n**Worst case: O(n²)**\n- Occurs when the pivot is always the smallest or largest element\n- This happens with already sorted arrays (when using first/last element as pivot)\n- Results in n levels of recursion, each processing up to n elements\n\nThe space complexity is O(log n) average case due to recursion stack, but O(n) in worst case.	{}	2026-02-03 10:47:37.926743
